  "why": "The paper provides partial diagnostic insight into discovered failures by characterizing where and when PAIR succeeds or fails (per-model and per-behavior category jailbreak rates, transferability, ablations on attacker prompts, and defended performance). These analyses reveal patterns (e.g., which models and behavior categories are more vulnerable, which attacker strategies are most effective, and how defenses affect success rates), which give actionable, high-level diagnostics. However, the paper does not trace failures to concrete underlying model vulnerabilities (e.g., corrupted or biased training data, spurious features, or internal model activations) nor provide causal analyses that link specific failure cases to such root causes. Therefore the appropriate rating is Medium.",
